snippet.textDisplay:
Is anyone else getting intense anxiety about the utter global incompetence regarding containment of this virus!?

I want more people to talk about the lack of test kits, even if we self isolate, once the containment phase one is lifted, with no testing kits, the virus will be close to untraceable passing person to person.

we need to talk about the reasons why China has handled it so well. It’s not just because they put the cities under lockdown. They enforced those restrictions vehemently so no ‘Florida spring break college kids’ could flout the social distancing & isolation rules.

And they had enough testing kits! In order to get a test you must have eg. come off an international flight, or flown in from China, or been in direct contact with someone who has tested positive for covid-19 (of which that person needs to be applicable to the above terms, and may have been asymptomatic for two weeks infecting others.

The massive quarantine holdings they built, putting patients who aren’t experiencing symptoms yet, but have it, into refurbished gymnasiums with beds and oxygen bottles at the corridors.
We don’t have that.

I wish this was being taken more seriously by the public, and for the government to have harsher regulations put in place.
We don’t have the testing kits (of which are only around 86% accurate)

We don’t have the space prepared for quarantined individuals (just send them home to quarantine, infecting their family)

We’re bailing out companies who sell useless commodities instead of using that money to go towards the things I mentioned above: employing all the people who were laid off to make more testing kits in factories, to build these quarantine strong holds (so it doesn’t spread to the patient’s families).

Car companies and nail salons shouldn’t be given govt bail out money, when they’ve laid off their staff anyway.

The government needs to stop messing about and FUND these researchers, so when a vaccine is achieved, it won’t be sold for $1,000 a syringe.
